00:12:42,859 --> 00:12:44,526
[HUGHES] In general,
men prefer to let their

252
00:12:44,526 --> 00:12:46,859
actions speak instead of words.

253
00:12:46,859 --> 00:12:48,192
[HUGHES] When they're in pain,
they don't want to

254
00:12:48,192 --> 00:12:51,592
burden anyone with it...
Not if they can help it.

255
00:12:51,592 --> 00:12:54,159
They don't want anyone
to worry about them.

256
00:12:54,159 --> 00:12:55,992
That's how they are.

257
00:12:58,626 --> 00:13:00,192
[HUGHES] Even so, there
may come a time when they'll

258
00:13:00,192 --> 00:13:02,959
ask for your help.

259
00:13:02,959 --> 00:13:04,059
And when they do...

260
00:13:04,059 --> 00:13:07,159
I know that you'll
be there for them.

261
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:08,926
[HUGHES]
Isn't that enough?

262
00:13:11,226 --> 00:13:13,926
Elicia, we want
to play...! Let's go!

263
00:13:13,926 --> 00:13:15,626
Will you put me down now?

264
00:13:15,626 --> 00:13:17,526
'Kay, down you go.

265
00:13:18,226 --> 00:13:19,626
Hey, you get away from her...!

266
00:13:19,626 --> 00:13:21,526
Elicia wants to play
with me not you!

267
00:13:21,526 --> 00:13:23,492
[BOY A] Huh? No way,
she's playing with me.

268
00:13:23,492 --> 00:13:25,459
She's quite the heartbreaker
already, isn't she?

269
00:13:25,459 --> 00:13:27,226
She picked me!

270
00:13:27,226 --> 00:13:28,092
- Come on,
Elicia!
- She picked me!

271
00:13:28,092 --> 00:13:28,592
- Come on, Elicia!
- Leave us alone!

272
00:13:28,592 --> 00:13:29,426
Listen up, boys...

273
00:13:29,426 --> 00:13:30,892
You try anything
with my daughter...

274
00:13:30,892 --> 00:13:32,759
and you'll answer to me.

275
00:13:32,759 --> 00:13:34,792
Your actions
speak too loudly!

276
00:13:39,759 --> 00:13:41,492
[GRACIA] Are you
sure you have to go?

277
00:13:41,492 --> 00:13:42,726
You're more than
welcome to stay

278
00:13:42,726 --> 00:13:44,892
with us for as long
as you're in town.

279
00:13:44,892 --> 00:13:47,926
I don't want to put you out
more than I have already.

280
00:13:49,859 --> 00:13:52,192
Elicia's gotten very
attached to you.

281
00:13:52,192 --> 00:13:53,459
[HUGHES LAUGHS]

282
00:13:53,459 --> 00:13:56,926
Well, would you look at that?
The two of you could be sisters.

283
00:13:56,926 --> 00:13:59,592
[ELICIA]
Sissy! Be safe, okay...?

284
00:13:59,592 --> 00:14:02,059
And come back and
visit me real soon!

285
00:14:02,059 --> 00:14:05,092
It's settled. You're staying
with us again tonight.

286
00:14:06,692 --> 00:14:08,226
[ELICIA AND WINRY LAUGH]

287
00:14:08,226 --> 00:14:10,926
It looks like I've
found myself a little sister.

288
00:14:17,692 --> 00:14:19,659
So we meet again,
you little bastard...

289
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:21,426
I'm not gonna
drink you...

290
00:14:22,959 --> 00:14:27,159
[AL] Brother, you have a living
body that needs nourishment.

291
00:14:27,159 --> 00:14:29,159
You have to drink it.

292
00:14:30,792 --> 00:14:33,126
[ED] I don't have to
if I don't want to...!

293
00:14:33,126 --> 00:14:35,792
It may not look like it,
but I have grown some...

294
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:39,192
But everyone still
calls me a pipsqueak!

295
00:14:39,192 --> 00:14:41,559
I wish I was like you, Al.

296
00:14:42,559 --> 00:14:44,859
You've got such a big body now.

297
00:14:46,992 --> 00:14:49,992
[AL] It's not like I asked
for this body, brother!

298
00:14:52,526 --> 00:14:55,159
[ED] S-Sorry...
You're right...

299
00:14:55,159 --> 00:14:57,659
It's my fault
that it happened...

300
00:14:57,659 --> 00:14:59,059
But I'll make it right...

301
00:14:59,059 --> 00:15:01,526
I'll get you back into
your real body, you'll see Al--

302
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:02,859
[AL] That's what
you always say!

303
00:15:02,859 --> 00:15:04,659
But you don't
know that for sure!

304
00:15:04,659 --> 00:15:06,792
Look-Look, I promise
I'm gonna get you back...

305
00:15:06,792 --> 00:15:08,459
Believe me Al, I'll do it!

306
00:15:08,459 --> 00:15:09,526
[AL] Believe you?!

307
00:15:09,526 --> 00:15:11,626
[AL] How am I supposed to
believe anything when

308
00:15:11,626 --> 00:15:13,692
I'm stuck in this body?!

309
00:15:13,692 --> 00:15:15,792
[AL] What should I believe in?
My memories?

310
00:15:15,792 --> 00:15:17,759
[AL] Memories are just
scraps of information

311
00:15:17,759 --> 00:15:20,526
that can be made up
as easily as anything else.

312
00:15:20,526 --> 00:15:22,759
Al, what... what are
you talking about?

313
00:15:22,759 --> 00:15:24,526
[AL] Do you remember when you
said there was something

314
00:15:24,526 --> 00:15:27,059
you were afraid to tell me?

315
00:15:27,059 --> 00:15:30,759
[AL] I think... I think I might
know what it was.

316
00:15:30,759 --> 00:15:33,559
[AL] Maybe you wanted to say
that my soul and my memories

317
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:37,592
are really artificial
constructions you created!

318
00:15:39,559 --> 00:15:42,659
[AL] You, Winry, and Granny...

319
00:15:42,659 --> 00:15:45,492
You've been lying to
me all along, haven't you?

320
00:15:45,492 --> 00:15:47,659
[AL] What do you have to
say for yourself, Brother?!

321
00:15:47,659 --> 00:15:49,426
[ED POUNDS TABLE]

322
00:15:50,959 --> 00:15:52,959
[ED] Is that what
you really think...?

323
00:15:52,959 --> 00:15:54,859
Have you believed
that all this time?

324
00:15:54,859 --> 00:15:56,492
[AL GASPS]

325
00:15:58,059 --> 00:15:59,792
So are you finished...

326
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:02,092
or is there more
you wanted to say.

327
00:16:07,692 --> 00:16:08,959
Okay.

328
00:16:18,892 --> 00:16:20,826
Don't go.

329
00:16:20,826 --> 00:16:21,992
Ed!

330
00:16:24,759 --> 00:16:26,792
[WINRY]
Al, you...

331
00:16:26,792 --> 00:16:28,792
Moron!!

332
00:16:28,792 --> 00:16:29,792
[METAL HITTING METAL]

333
00:16:29,792 --> 00:16:30,992
[SHOCKED]

334
00:16:32,386 --> 00:16:33,770
[AL] Where did
that come from?

335
00:16:33,770 --> 00:16:35,770
[WINRY BREATHING HEAVY]

336
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:41,003
[AL]
Winry...!

337
00:16:41,003 --> 00:16:42,137
[WINRY]
You idiot!

338
00:16:42,137 --> 00:16:43,103
[METAL ON METAL]

339
00:16:43,103 --> 00:16:46,270
You have no idea
how Ed feels!

340
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:49,870
Do you know what he was
so afraid to talk to you about?

341
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:51,937
He wants to know if
you blame him for what

342
00:16:51,937 --> 00:16:54,270
happened to your body, Al!

343
00:16:56,237 --> 00:16:57,137
It's all my fault.

344
00:16:57,137 --> 00:16:59,670
Al lost his body,
and it's all my fault.

345
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:00,437
He can't eat anymore.

346
00:17:00,437 --> 00:17:01,370
He can't sleep.

347
00:17:01,370 --> 00:17:03,170
He can't feel cold or warmth...

348
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:05,703
He's my little brother
and I'm supposed to protect him,

349
00:17:05,703 --> 00:17:07,737
and I did this.

350
00:17:07,737 --> 00:17:09,670
[ED] How could
he ever forgive me?

351
00:17:09,670 --> 00:17:12,303
Al isn't the type of boy
who would resent you for this...

352
00:17:12,303 --> 00:17:14,403
Just ask him and I'm
sure you'll see.

353
00:17:14,403 --> 00:17:17,803
No... I'm... I'm too afraid

354
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:20,103
I'm too scared
of what he'll say.

355
00:17:20,103 --> 00:17:22,137
[METAL CLANK]

356
00:17:22,137 --> 00:17:25,737
And then, you idiot...

357
00:17:25,737 --> 00:17:27,303
...you said that!

358
00:17:27,303 --> 00:17:29,803
[WINRY SOBBING]

359
00:17:29,803 --> 00:17:32,170
Who would ever do
something like that...?

360
00:17:32,170 --> 00:17:34,737
Who would be prepared
to risk his own life...

361
00:17:34,737 --> 00:17:37,370
to create a fake brother?

362
00:17:38,237 --> 00:17:40,270
[WINRY]
Don't you get it...?

363
00:17:40,270 --> 00:17:46,003
All the two of you
have left... is each other.

364
00:17:46,003 --> 00:17:48,737
[AL] Now go
get your brother!

365
00:17:51,437 --> 00:17:52,703
Start running!

366
00:17:52,703 --> 00:17:53,870
[AL]
Right!

367
00:17:58,037 --> 00:18:00,637
[BREEZE BLOWING]

368
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:10,237
[AL] Broth--

369
00:18:10,237 --> 00:18:11,270
- [ED] You know something, Al...
- [AL] Broth--

370
00:18:11,270 --> 00:18:13,103
[ED] We haven't had
a good fight in awhile...

371
00:18:13,103 --> 00:18:14,670
I'm starting to get flabby.

372
00:18:14,670 --> 00:18:15,970
[AL]
Huh?

373
00:18:24,137 --> 00:18:26,103
[AL]
Huh...? Hey!

374
00:18:28,137 --> 00:18:30,703
[AL]
Hold on, Brother!

375
00:18:30,703 --> 00:18:32,003
Stop!

376
00:18:33,370 --> 00:18:35,903
Your wounds haven't
healed enough for this.

377
00:18:43,037 --> 00:18:45,070
I beat you!

378
00:18:45,070 --> 00:18:47,037
The first time I ever won.

379
00:18:49,903 --> 00:18:51,737
That wasn't a
fair fight, Brother.

380
00:18:51,737 --> 00:18:52,570
Don't give me that.

381
00:18:52,570 --> 00:18:56,103
A win is a win,
and you know it, Al.

382
00:18:56,103 --> 00:18:57,770
We've always fought like this...

383
00:18:57,770 --> 00:19:01,137
ever since we
were really little.

384
00:19:01,137 --> 00:19:02,870
Now that I think about it,
we've fought over some

385
00:19:02,870 --> 00:19:04,970
really stupid
things, haven't we?

386
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:08,203
[AL] Definitely. Like who would
get the top and bottom bunks.

387
00:19:08,203 --> 00:19:09,670
[ED] Yeah.

388
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:11,437
[AL] We fought over
candy a lot too, huh?

389
00:19:11,437 --> 00:19:13,403
[ED] And that toy,
you remember?

390
00:19:13,403 --> 00:19:14,870
[AL] I won that one.

391
00:19:14,870 --> 00:19:16,803
[AL] And when we played
in the Rain River, too.

392
00:19:16,803 --> 00:19:19,303
[ED] Oh yeah, you shoved
me into the water.

393
00:19:19,303 --> 00:19:21,237
[AL] And that fight we
had during our training.

394
00:19:21,237 --> 00:19:22,803
[ED] Teacher said
we were being too loud,

395
00:19:22,803 --> 00:19:24,370
then she beat us up herself...

396
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:26,270
Why don't we
call that one a draw?

397
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:27,770
[AL] We even
fought over which

398
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:29,737
one of us would marry
Winry someday.

399
00:19:29,737 --> 00:19:30,503
What...?!

400
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:31,537
[ED] I don't
remember that one!

401
00:19:31,537 --> 00:19:34,437
[AL] I won the fight...
but she shot me down.

402
00:19:34,437 --> 00:19:36,337
Oh... did she?

403
00:19:44,470 --> 00:19:47,370
You're telling me that
all those memories are lies?

404
00:19:47,370 --> 00:19:48,903
[AL]
Sorry.

405
00:19:48,903 --> 00:19:50,737
[ED] And your determination
to be whole again,

406
00:19:50,737 --> 00:19:52,837
to get your body back,
no matter what...

407
00:19:52,837 --> 00:19:55,003
that's a lie too?

408
00:19:55,003 --> 00:19:56,703
[AL]
No, it's not a lie.

409
00:19:56,703 --> 00:19:58,070
[ED]
That's right!

410
00:19:58,070 --> 00:20:00,003
[ED] We're in this
together, all the way.

411
00:20:00,003 --> 00:20:00,870
[ED] Don't forget that,

412
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:03,137
and we're gonna
keep pushing forward...

413
00:20:03,137 --> 00:20:04,870
We'll make ourselves stronger,

414
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,737
faster and better
until we get our bodies back.

415
00:20:07,737 --> 00:20:08,403
[AL GIGGLES]

416
00:20:08,403 --> 00:20:09,870
[AL]
And the milk?

417
00:20:09,870 --> 00:20:10,903
[ED]
Milk...?!

418
00:20:10,903 --> 00:20:13,270
Fine, I'll drink a little.

419
00:20:13,270 --> 00:20:15,403
[ED AND AL LAUGH]

420
00:20:15,403 --> 00:20:17,637
[ED] Whatever
it takes, Brother.

421
00:20:19,303 --> 00:20:21,037
[WINRY]
Mr. Hughes.

422
00:20:21,037 --> 00:20:23,170
Maybe you don't have
to hear something out loud,

423
00:20:23,170 --> 00:20:25,937
but it sure is
helpful sometimes.

424
00:20:27,203 --> 00:20:29,037
I guess it is.

425
00:20:36,137 --> 00:20:40,137
[STRONG WINDS]

426
00:20:45,903 --> 00:20:48,170
[SCAR]
My brother...

427
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:49,703
Master...

428
00:20:49,703 --> 00:20:51,670
They're gone... all gone.

429
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:54,070
[KIMBLEE]
Hey!

430
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:56,903
[SCAR] You don't look like
an Ishvalan. Who are you?

431
00:20:56,903 --> 00:20:58,803
[KIMBLEE] Oh my,
where are my manners...?

432
00:20:58,803 --> 00:21:01,070
I should have
introduced myself.

433
00:21:01,070 --> 00:21:03,870
I'm a State Alchemist
sent here by the military...

434
00:21:03,870 --> 00:21:06,803
I've been sent to
exterminate this sector.

435
00:21:14,070 --> 00:21:16,070
Hey...! You're awake!

436
00:21:17,203 --> 00:21:18,203
Where am I?

437
00:21:18,203 --> 00:21:20,270
In a slum
outside of East City.

438
00:21:20,270 --> 00:21:23,137
You're among friends now.

439
00:21:23,137 --> 00:21:25,837
Who are you...?
You, old man.

440
00:21:25,837 --> 00:21:29,370
Me? Why, I'm a man of
Ishvala, just as you are, son...

441
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:31,303
There's nothing
to worry about here...

442
00:21:31,303 --> 00:21:33,403
I won't sell out
one of my own.

443
00:21:33,403 --> 00:21:35,337
Are we the only ones here...?

444
00:21:35,337 --> 00:21:37,437
Are there other
Ishvalan survivors?

445
00:21:37,437 --> 00:21:39,837
Yes... indeed there are...

446
00:21:39,837 --> 00:21:41,203
A run-down slum such as

447
00:21:41,203 --> 00:21:44,070
this may bear no resemblance
to our ancestral home...

448
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:45,337
but you know
what they say...

449
00:21:45,337 --> 00:21:49,303
"the world is god's bosom"...
our great, loving god Ishvala...

450
00:21:49,303 --> 00:21:50,303
Am I right?

451
00:21:50,303 --> 00:21:52,070
[OLD MAN LAUGHS]

452
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:54,803
Yes, you certainly are.

453
00:21:54,803 --> 00:21:56,370
You can't, you're not ready!

454
00:21:56,370 --> 00:21:58,270
We found you
floating in the sewers.

455
00:21:58,270 --> 00:22:00,303
You were hurt bad.

456
00:22:08,170 --> 00:22:10,003
Boy... My right arm.

457
00:22:10,003 --> 00:22:12,037
Did I lose it,
or is it still with me?

458
00:22:12,037 --> 00:22:13,303
Yeah, it's still there, mister.

459
00:22:13,303 --> 00:22:15,170
It should be fine.

460
00:22:17,303 --> 00:22:18,803
Your tattoo...

461
00:22:18,803 --> 00:22:20,370
It's really amazing.

462
00:22:21,870 --> 00:22:27,437
Yes... it's important
to me... a precious gift.

463
00:22:27,437 --> 00:22:29,670
From my family.

464
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:07,408
<i>[NARRATOR] A good friend
became a comrade in arms...</i>

465
00:24:07,408 --> 00:24:11,861
<i>and over time his presence
was taken for granted.</i>

466
00:24:11,861 --> 00:24:13,828
<i>Although the future
they once dreamed of</i>

467
00:24:13,828 --> 00:24:16,228
<i>became bleaker than they
had ever imagined...</i>

468
00:24:16,228 --> 00:24:19,195
<i>this good friend
was always there by his side,</i>

469
00:24:19,195 --> 00:24:20,928
<i>where he belonged.</i>

470
00:24:20,928 --> 00:24:24,928
<i>Next time, on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood--</i>

471
00:24:24,928 --> 00:24:28,828
<i>Episode Ten.
Separate Destinations.</i>

472
00:24:28,828 --> 00:24:30,995
<i>A friend whose presence
comes as naturally</i>

473
00:24:30,995 --> 00:24:33,595
<i>as breathing can
never be replaced.</i>

